description: Aspose.Imaging for .NET is an imaging library that lets developers create, edit, draw or convert images in their .NET applications. Aspose.Imaging provides features that go beyond the native capabilities of the development platform. It works independent of other applications and although Aspose.Imaging allows you to save to Adobe PhotoShop® format (PSD), you do not need PhotoShop on the machine.
releaseNotes:
Aspose.Imaging for .Net has been updated to version 3.6.0 and we are pleased to announce it.
      The following is a list of changes in this version of Aspose.Imaging.
      
      New features:
      IMAGING-35315 Support merging PSD layers when converting to a JPG
      IMAGING-35301 Support export Emf/Emf+ files to raster formats
      IMAGING-35078 Support for Metafile (EMF) in .Net
      
      Enhancements:
      IMAGING-35317 Converting PSD to TIFF is producing incorrect TIFF image [.Net]
      IMAGING-35302 Improve memory usage while rendering emf/emf+ files
      IMAGING-35198 Aspose.Imaging drawing engine stage by stage introduction in part of enabling of own drawing engine usage
      IMAGING-34796 Verify all raster image operations so that watermarks are not duplicated
      
      Exceptions
      IMAGING-35240 WebPWriterTest.WriteLosslessDataTest sometimes an Exception OutOfMemory
